The paper deals with the study of infinite words and subshifts, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of algebraic geometry suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses periodic configurations, which are related to dynamical systems (cs.DS) and the concept of pattern complexity, which is a topic in logic and computation (cs.LO).
